complaints.summary: TOLD BY PATT LOBB TOYOTA IN MCKINNEY, TX THAT TOYOTA NA WILL BE REACHING OUT TO ME.  "UNABLE TO REPLACE STEERING WHEEL" UNDER RECALL 91V223

FOR YEARS I HAVE BEEN RECEIVING A RECALL NOTICE FROM TOYOTA EVERY FEW MONTHS. I THINK IT IS FOR AIRBAGS, BUT I'M NOT SURE. THE NOTICE ALWAYS SAYS TO CALL MY LOCAL DEALER, WHICH I HAVE DONE A FEW TIMES WITHOUT ANY SATISFACTION. THE LAST TIME I PURSUED THE REPAIR MORE VIGOROUSLY, AND TOYOTA TOLD ME THEY NO LONGER HAVE THE REPAIR KITS AND SO CANNOT FIX MY CAR. NOW I HAVE JUST RECEIVED ANOTHER RECALL NOTICE FOR THE SAME ISSUE, WHICH IS CLEARLY AN IMPORTANT SAFETY ISSUE. I WANT THE CAR REPAIRED.
I WAS CHECKING FOR THE TAKATA AIRBAG RECALL AND FOUND THIS RECALL WHICH INCLUDES STEERING WHEEL AND AIRBAG(91V223) AND THE TOYOTA DEALERSHIP SAYS IT IS TO OLD OF A RECALL TO FIX.
NHTSA REFERENCE ID 91V223.   ESCONDIDO TOYOTA SAYS THEY CAN'T REPLACE THE STEERING WHEEL.

DT*:  THE CONTACT STATED WHILE DRIVING 65 MPH ONE OF THE TWO THROTTLE BODY SPRINGS FRACTURED CAUSING THE VEHICLE TO ACCELERATE TO 80 MPH.  THE IGNITION WAS TURNED OFF SEVERAL TIMES SO THE VEHICLE COULD BE SAFELY MANEUVERED OFF THE ROAD.  THE DEALER WAS ALERTED AND DETERMINED THE ENTIRE THROTTLE BODY MUST BE REPLACED.  THE MANUFACTURER HAS NOT BEEN ALERTED.

DRIVING ON INTERSTATE AT 65 MPH HOOD FLEW UP AND SHATTERED WINDSHIELD AND T-TOP GLASS. SECONDARY LATCH FAILED TO CATCH HOOD FROM FLIGHT AND RESULTED IN HOOD, HOOD LATCH, WIPER COWL, WINDSHIELD, AND T-TOP DAMAGE. NO ACTION TAKEN TO CORRECT FAILURE. SOME REPAIRS HAVE BEEN MADE TO GLASS. THIS HAS HAPPENED 3 TIMES IN THE SAME MODEL OF VEHICLE, 3 DIFFERENT CARS.

WHILE DRIVING AT APPROXIMATELY 35 MPH, CONSUMER HEARD A FLAPPING TYPE NOISE THAT SOUNDED LIKE A BELT HAD COME LOOSE.  THE VEHICLE IMMEDIATELY DIED.  CONSUMER WAS INFORMED THAT THE ENGINE HAD FROZEN IN THE EVENT THE VEHICLE HAD RAN OUT OF OIL, HOWEVER THERE WAS FRESH OIL IN THE VEHICLE AND NO SIGNS OF LACK OF OIL.   DEALERSHIP ADDED THAT THE ENGINE COULD FREEZE IF THE VEHICLE HAD AT ANY TIME RUN LOW ON OIL.  ENGINE HAD TO BE REPLACED.  *TT

WHILE DRIVING, A FIRE STARTED IN THE ENGINE COMPARTMENT, LOCATED IN THE REAR OF THE VEHICLE, THERE WAS NO DAMAGE TO THE ACTUAL BODY OF THE CAR,THE ONLY VISIBLE DAMAGE TO THE UNIT WAS TO THE ENGINE, (OHIO TRAFFIC CRASH REPORT).  *TT

WHILE DRIVING, A FIRE STARTED IN THE ENGINE COMPARTMENT, LOCATED IN THE REAR OF THE VEHICLE, THERE WAS NO DAMAGE TO THE ACTUAL BODY OF THE CAR,THE ONLY VISIBLE DAMAGE TO THE UNIT WAS TO THE ENGINE, (OHIO TRAFFIC CRASH REPORT).  *TT
DRIVER'S SIDE DOOR WOULD NOT OPEN FROM EITHER SIDE OF VEHICLE. DEALER NOTIFIED, AND WOULD NOT REPAIR UNLESS COST GOES TO CONSUMER.  *AK
AIR BAG DEPLOYMENT WAS VIOLENT, CAUSING MULTIPLE BRUISES, HEARING LOSS IN BOTH EARS,CERVICAL STRAIN, SEVERE BRUISING TO BOTH THUMBS, AND LOOSENED LOWER BRIDGE IN MOUTH.

DRIVELINE FLIPPED OUT FROM UNDERNEATH VEHICLE AHEAD, WENT UNDERNEATH PLAINTIFF'S VEHICLE, IMPACTED ON THE UNDER CARRIAGE, CAUSING AIR BAG TO FALSELY DEPLOY, RESULTING IN ACCIDENT, MULTIPLE BRUISES AND HEARING LOSS.
BRIDGESTONE TIRES WEAR PREMATURELY, CAUSING INSTABILITY.

issues.title: Snap Ring Failure in Manual Transmission
issues.description: The snap ring in the manual transmission (C52/C56) can break, causing loss of 5th gear and potentially damaging internal transmission components. This is a well-documented failure mode that affects a significant percentage of SW20 MR2s.
issues.fix_description: Replace snap ring with updated part, inspect and replace damaged gears if necessary, rebuild transmission
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive shifting, preemptive snap ring replacement

issues.title: Engine Oil Starvation and Bearing Failure
issues.description: The 3S-GTE engine can suffer oil starvation during aggressive cornering due to oil pan design and pickup tube location, leading to rod bearing failure and engine destruction.
issues.fix_description: Engine rebuild with aftermarket oil pan, accusump system, or improved oil pickup design
issues.prevention: Install aftermarket oil pan or accusump, maintain proper oil levels, avoid track use without modifications

issues.title: Turbocharger CT26 Failure
issues.description: The stock CT26 turbocharger is prone to shaft bearing wear, wheel damage, and oil seal failure, especially at higher mileage or when boost levels are increased.
issues.fix_description: Turbocharger rebuild or replacement, check and replace oil feed/drain lines
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes, proper warm-up and cool-down procedures, avoid boost increases without supporting mods

issues.title: Head Gasket Failure
issues.description: The 3S-GTE engine is prone to head gasket failure, particularly between cylinders or to the cooling system, often caused by overheating or detonation.
issues.fix_description: Head gasket replacement, cylinder head resurfacing, ARP head studs installation
issues.prevention: Maintain cooling system, use quality coolant, avoid overheating and detonation

issues.title: Clutch Master and Slave Cylinder Failure
issues.description: The hydraulic clutch system components, particularly the master and slave cylinders, are prone to internal seal failure causing clutch engagement issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace master and slave cylinders, bleed hydraulic system, replace clutch fluid
issues.prevention: Regular clutch fluid changes, avoid riding the clutch pedal

issues.title: Radiator and Cooling System Issues
issues.description: The compact engine bay and dual radiator setup make cooling system maintenance critical. Radiators are prone to clogging and failure, leading to overheating.
issues.fix_description: Replace radiators, flush cooling system, upgrade to aluminum radiators
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, proper bleeding procedures, avoid overheating

issues.title: Electrical Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators, particularly on the driver's side, commonly fail due to worn cables and weak motors, causing windows to drop or bind.
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator assembly, lubricate tracks, replace window motor if needed
issues.prevention: Regular lubrication of window tracks, avoid forcing stuck windows

issues.title: Fuel Pump and Fuel System Issues
issues.description: The high-pressure fuel pump can fail, and fuel lines are prone to degradation, causing fuel delivery problems and potential fire hazards.
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump, fuel filter, and degraded fuel lines, clean fuel system
issues.prevention: Regular fuel filter changes, use quality fuel, replace aging fuel lines

issues.title: Suspension Bushings Deterioration
issues.description: Rubber suspension bushings throughout the vehicle deteriorate over time, affecting handling and causing alignment issues and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn bushings with OEM or polyurethane alternatives, perform alignment
issues.prevention: Regular inspection, avoid harsh driving conditions, replace bushings proactively

issues.title: T-Top Seal Leakage
issues.description: T-Top equipped models commonly experience water leaks due to deteriorated seals around the removable roof panels.
issues.fix_description: Replace T-Top seals, adjust panel alignment, clean and lubricate latches
issues.prevention: Regular seal inspection and cleaning, proper storage of T-Top panels

issues.title: ECU Capacitor Failure
issues.description: The engine control unit contains electrolytic capacitors that fail over time, causing various engine management issues and potential no-start conditions.
issues.fix_description: ECU capacitor replacement or ECU rebuild, professional soldering required
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, regular ECU inspection, proactive capacitor replacement

editorial.tagline: Japan's mid-engine masterpiece that bites back
editorial.hero_blurb: The SW20 MR2 Turbo represents Toyota's bold swing at Ferrari territory, delivering exotic mid-engine thrills with Japanese reliability. This is raw, unfiltered driving pleasure that demands respect and rewards skill.
editorial.essence: The SW20 MR2 Turbo is Toyota's most ambitious sports car, combining mid-engine layout with turbocharged fury. It's a machine that captures the spirit of late 80s/early 90s Japanese performance excess, offering supercar dynamics at a fraction of the cost.
editorial.heritage: Born from Toyota's desire to create a pure sports car, the MR2 evolved from the lightweight AW11 into the more muscular SW20 generation. Drawing inspiration from Ferrari and Porsche, Toyota engineered their own interpretation of the mid-engine formula, creating something uniquely Japanese in character.
editorial.design_philosophy: Toyota aimed to build an affordable exotic that could challenge European supercars while maintaining Japanese practicality. The design emphasized pure driving dynamics over comfort, with mid-engine placement for optimal weight distribution and the 3S-GTE turbo motor for serious punch.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not a factory racing weapon, the SW20 MR2 found success in amateur motorsport and time attack events. Its mid-engine layout and turbocharged power made it a natural choice for track enthusiasts seeking affordable speed.
editorial.engine_character: The 3S-GTE delivers classic turbo character with a healthy dose of lag followed by explosive power delivery. It's an engine that builds drama, rewarding patience with a surge of boost that pushes you deep into your seat when the turbo spools up.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 5-speed manual offers precise, mechanical shifts with satisfying weight. Gate spacing is perfect for quick direction changes, though the clutch can be heavy in stop-and-go traffic.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Mid-engine magic with a dark side - the MR2 is brilliantly balanced when driven within limits but can snap into oversteer without warning. The chassis rewards smooth, progressive inputs with incredible agility and cornering capability.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic steering provides excellent feedback and perfect weighting. You can feel exactly what the front wheels are doing, with enough assistance for parking but pure communication at speed.
editorial.brake_confidence: Strong, progressive brakes that inspire confidence with excellent pedal feel. The mid-engine weight distribution helps prevent nose dive under hard braking, maintaining stability when threshold braking.
editorial.sound_signature: A distinctive turbo whistle builds to a satisfying whoosh, backed by the mechanical symphony of the 3S-GTE. The exhaust note is purposeful rather than melodic, with pops and crackles on overrun.
editorial.ideal_owner: Experienced enthusiasts who understand and appreciate lift-off oversteer, enjoy the ritual of turbo lag, and want an exotic experience without exotic maintenance costs. Perfect for drivers who value character over convenience.
editorial.not_ideal_for: New drivers, those seeking daily driver comfort, or anyone wanting predictable, forgiving handling. The snap oversteer and cramped interior make it unsuitable for casual drivers or long commutes.
editorial.buyers_summary: Find the cleanest example possible as rust and neglect are common enemies. Turbo motors require careful maintenance, so comprehensive service records are essential. Budget for potential snap ring failure and cooling system refresh.
